WEBVTT

00:04.938 --> 00:05.905 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Good evening.

00:05.939 --> 00:07.741 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
I'm Judy Woodruff.

00:07.774 --> 00:13.013 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
On the "NewsHour" tonight: A
massive blast
rocks Kabul, leaving at least 90
dead, hundreds

00:13.046 --> 00:18.518 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
wounded, and an entire city
block in ruin
in the diplomatic hub of
Afghanistan's capital.

00:18.551 --> 00:20.353 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
Then:

00:20.387 --> 00:24.157 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
PETER WITTIG, German Ambassador
to the United
States: The U.S. would find
itself in an odd

00:24.190 --> 00:26.926 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
company, just with Syria and
Nicaragua.

00:26.960 --> 00:32.098 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: With reports the
Trump administration
may pull the U.S. out of the
Paris climate

00:32.132 --> 00:37.937 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
accord, I sit down with
Germany's ambassador
to talk about the growing rift
between Berlin

00:37.971 --> 00:39.472 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
and Washington.

00:39.506 --> 00:43.777 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And part two of our look at how
we treat premature
babies.

00:43.810 --> 00:49.349 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Can the simplest emotional
connections help
combat the stress of premature
birth?

00:49.382 --> 00:51.051 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
DR.

00:51.084 --> 00:55.355 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
MARTHA WELCH, Columbia
University: The child
is bombarded with sounds and
light.

00:55.388 --> 01:00.527 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
It's antithetical to what the
brain needs
and the child needs for
development.

01:00.560 --> 01:04.497 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
So, what we're doing is trying
to make up
for that.

01:04.531 --> 01:07.600 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: All that and more
on tonight's
"PBS NewsHour."

01:07.634 --> 01:11.871 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
(BREAK)

01:11.905 --> 01:24.050 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: The situation is
deteriorating
day by day.

01:24.084 --> 01:29.756 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Those were the words of one of
Afghanistan's
lawmakers after a huge truck
bomb devastated

01:29.789 --> 01:31.391 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
part of Kabul today.

01:31.424 --> 01:35.962 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
It killed at least 90 people,
and wounded
400 more.

01:35.995 --> 01:39.466 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
Chief foreign affairs
correspondent Margaret
Warner has our report.

01:39.499 --> 01:45.805 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MARGARET WARNER: A pall of black
smoke, sirens
wailing, chaos in the streets.

01:45.839 --> 01:52.445 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
A gigantic suicide bomb had
detonated in the
highly secured heart of the
Afghan capital.

01:52.479 --> 01:58.384 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The tremendous force of the
blast gouged out
a 15-foot crater and blew out
windows as far

01:58.418 --> 02:00.186 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
as half-a-mile away.

02:00.220 --> 02:05.125 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
RAHIM, Afghanistan (through
translator): The
explosion took place the minute
we sat down.

02:05.158 --> 02:08.461 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
After the explosion, we hurried
downstairs
and saw all the things damaged.

02:08.495 --> 02:10.330 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Many buildings were badly
destroyed.

02:10.363 --> 02:15.568 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
MARGARET WARNER: Special
correspondent Jennifer
Glasse in Kabul, who spoke to us
via Skype,

02:15.602 --> 02:17.370 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
said the bombing came as a jolt.

02:17.403 --> 02:22.609 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JENNIFER GLASSE: It's been quiet
here in the
Afghan capital for the last
couple of weeks,

02:22.642 --> 02:23.576 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
almost eerily quiet.

02:23.610 --> 02:24.878 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
The weather's been beautiful.

02:24.911 --> 02:27.180 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
People have been going out for
picnics.

02:27.213 --> 02:36.189 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The scale of this attack is
really unprecedented,
the worst we believe since 2001,
and that

02:36.222 --> 02:38.758 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
is such a terrible, terrible
shock to people.

02:38.791 --> 02:43.163 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MARGARET WARNER: The bomb hidden
in a septic
tank cleaning truck rocked the
diplomatic

02:43.196 --> 02:45.865 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
quarter at the height of morning
rush hour.

02:45.899 --> 02:51.204 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Despite its fortified blast
wall, Germany's
embassy suffered extensive
damage.

02:51.237 --> 02:56.442 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The bomb site was also close to
the Afghan
presidential palace and defense
ministry.

02:56.476 --> 03:02.549 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The U.S. Embassy is about a mile
away, yet
11 American contractors were
hurt.

03:02.582 --> 03:06.953 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Scores of the wounded were
rushed to nearby
hospitals, where some told of
surviving the

03:06.986 --> 03:08.321 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
blast.

03:08.354 --> 03:11.658 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MAN (through translator):
Everything was destroyed
in my location.

03:11.691 --> 03:12.659 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
I don't know what happened.

03:12.692 --> 03:14.093 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
There were lots of workers.

03:14.127 --> 03:15.562 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
A lot of people were martyred.

03:15.595 --> 03:17.363 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
All the people who were on the
street were
killed.

03:17.397 --> 03:21.801 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MARGARET WARNER: In Nuremberg,
German Chancellor
Angela Merkel condemned the
attack.

03:21.834 --> 03:26.906 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
ANGELA MERKEL, German Chancellor
(through
translator): In moments like
these, it is

03:26.940 --> 03:31.244 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
once again clear to us that
terrorism knows
no boundaries.

03:31.277 --> 03:37.150 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
All of us who believe in the
rights, the freedom
and the dignity of mankind in
Europe, America,

03:37.183 --> 03:43.156 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
in Africa, and of course also in
Afghanistan
will wage the battle against
terrorists and

03:43.189 --> 03:44.991 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
we will win.

03:45.024 --> 03:48.494 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MARGARET WARNER: Today's bombing
is just the
latest in a string of attacks
that have racked

03:48.528 --> 03:50.663 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
the Afghan capital.

03:50.697 --> 03:53.499 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
Security conditions have
deteriorated sharply.

03:53.533 --> 03:58.605 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And hundreds of Afghans have
been killed in
bombings from both a resurgent
Taliban and

03:58.638 --> 04:02.342 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
a growing faction of the Islamic
State.

04:02.375 --> 04:08.248 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Jennifer Glasse says the Afghan
security forces'
failure to protect them have
roiled the country's

04:08.281 --> 04:09.682 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
citizens.

04:09.716 --> 04:11.784 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JENNIFER GLASSE: There's a lot
of anger here
among the Afghan people.

04:11.818 --> 04:16.856 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
How this large truck got into
this part of
Kabul, heavily fortified --
you're not allowed

04:16.889 --> 04:18.558 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
to have big trucks in the center
of Kabul
during the daytime for security
reasons and

04:18.591 --> 04:20.360 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
for traffic reasons.

04:20.393 --> 04:28.701 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And so there are a lot of
questions among
the Afghan people how this could
have possibly

04:28.735 --> 04:30.670 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
happened.

04:30.703 --> 04:33.506 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MARGARET WARNER: The Taliban
denied responsibility
for today's blast, and in fact
condemned it.

04:33.539 --> 04:40.847 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JENNIFER GLASSE: We have seen
this before,
especially in cases where there
have been

04:40.880 --> 04:47.587 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
large civilian causalities and a
potential
for a public backlash, that the
Taliban, sometimes,

04:47.620 --> 04:49.455 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
