the attack,
deny that the attack was theirs.

04:49.489 --> 04:52.225 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MARGARET WARNER: Afghan troops
have suffered
heavy losses over the past year,
as the Taliban

04:52.258 --> 04:55.128 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
has made gains across the
countryside.

04:55.161 --> 05:01.100 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Now the Trump administration has
signaled
it plans to take a more
aggressive role there.

05:01.134 --> 05:06.072 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Reports surfaced earlier this
month that the
president is considering sending
5,000 more

05:06.105 --> 05:10.410 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
U.S. troops to support the 8,000
already on
the ground.

05:10.443 --> 05:12.378 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
Again, Jennifer Glasse:

05:12.412 --> 05:15.114 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JENNIFER GLASSE: The idea is to
get more international
forces a little closer to the
ground level

05:15.148 --> 05:18.384 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
to guide the Afghan security
forces in the
field, to get them a little bit
more coordinated,

05:18.418 --> 05:27.860 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
and to make them a little more
effective in
the fight against the Taliban.

05:27.894 --> 05:36.169 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
They're right now taking
punishing casualties,
losing 15, sometimes 20 soldiers
a day across

05:36.202 --> 05:37.970 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
the country.

05:38.004 --> 05:39.839 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MARGARET WARNER: The U.S. also
has stepped
up airstrikes and raids against
the Islamic

05:39.872 --> 05:44.077 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
State group that's now active in
Eastern Afghanistan.

05:44.110 --> 05:48.815 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
Last month, in a highly
publicized move, the
U.S. dropped its most powerful
conventional

05:48.848 --> 05:51.818 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
bomb on ISIS hideout there.

05:51.851 --> 05:54.687 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
For the "PBS NewsHour," I'm
Margaret Warner.

05:54.721 --> 06:00.293 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: President Trump
spoke by phone
today with Afghan President
Ashraf Ghani.

06:00.326 --> 06:03.629 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The White House said the U.S.
condemns the
attack.

06:03.663 --> 06:08.968 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
In the day's other news: There's
word that
ousted FBI Director James Comey
will testify

06:09.001 --> 06:13.873 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
