injured.

10:37.269 --> 10:40.439 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Others who work at the embassy,
one died,
another severely injured.

10:40.473 --> 10:46.545 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Does this give your government
pause, does
it give you second thoughts
about the commitment

10:46.579 --> 10:48.414 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
you have made to NATO in
Afghanistan?

10:48.447 --> 10:56.489 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
PETER WITTIG: Well, this is an
atrocious and
horrible attack once again in
the center of

10:56.522 --> 11:03.262 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Kabul, hurting not only German
citizens or
injuring or killing them, but
also a lot of

11:03.295 --> 11:04.930 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
Afghan civilians.

11:04.964 --> 11:11.804 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But this is no reason for us to
waver in our
commitment to stabilize
Afghanistan.

11:11.837 --> 11:15.941 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
We have been there together with
the U.S.
from the outset.

11:15.975 --> 11:18.611 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
