49:19.456 --> 49:23.593 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
HELEN MIRREN, Actress: For the
moments when
you are challenged by other
fears, like, oh,

49:23.627 --> 49:29.499 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
am I good enough, am I smart
enough, will
I fail, throw caution to the
winds.

49:29.533 --> 49:34.805 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Look fear straight away in its
ugly face,
and barge forward.

49:34.838 --> 49:39.109 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And when you get past it, turn
around, give
it a good swift kick in the ass.

49:39.142 --> 49:43.280 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JOSEPH BIDEN, Former Vice
President of the
United States: Treat people with
dignity.

49:43.313 --> 49:45.515 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
You demand it for yourself.

49:45.549 --> 49:48.218 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
You demand that you be treated
that way.

49:48.251 --> 49:55.092 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And all of us, all of us have to
do better
when it comes to building the
bonds of empathy,

49:55.125 --> 50:03.166 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
that folks who aren't like us,
aren't like
us, can know we understand them.

50:03.200 --> 50:06.737 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
DAVEED DIGGS, Actor: The best
advice that
I can give to those of you who
are worried

50:06.770 --> 50:11.842 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
about the when of the rest of
your life is
stop tripping.

50:11.875 --> 50:16.847 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I'm sure you will all have long
lists of accomplishments
and multiple rebirths.

50:16.880 --> 50:20.317 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
Some of you will have
accomplishments that
are asked to speak at colleges
or other prestigious

50:20.350 --> 50:21.318 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
institutions.

50:21.351 --> 50:22.319 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
Dope.

50:22.352 --> 50:23.320 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
Do that.

50:23.353 --> 50:25.222 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
(LAUGHTER)

50:25.255 --> 50:28.091 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
HILLARY RODHAM CLINTON, Former
U.S. Secretary
of State: So, whatever your
dreams are today,

50:28.125 --> 50:30.193 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
dream even bigger.

50:30.227 --> 50:35.232 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Wherever you have set your
sights, raise them
even higher.

50:35.265 --> 50:38.835 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
And, above all, keep going.

50:38.869 --> 50:41.805 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Don't do it because I asked you
to.

50:41.838 --> 50:43.540 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
Do it for yourselves.

50:43.573 --> 50:47.544 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
KATHRYN THORNTON, Former NASA
Astronaut: And
to our graduates, to whom we are
trusting

50:47.577 --> 50:52.115 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
nothing less than the future of
the human
race, I will share with you the
astronaut's

50:52.149 --> 50:53.483 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
prayer.

50:53.517 --> 50:58.255 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
It goes: Dear lord, please don't
let me mess
up.

50:58.288 --> 50:59.656 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
Amen.

50:59.689 --> 51:01.058 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
(LAUGHTER)

51:01.091 --> 51:06.963 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
KATHRYN THORNTON: Good luck and
Godspeed,
class of 2017.

51:06.997 --> 51:07.964 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
(CHEERING AND APPLAUSE)

51:07.998 --> 51:09.866 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Great advice, all
of that.

51:09.900 --> 51:13.637 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So, later this evening on PBS,
"NOVA" is presenting
a film that takes a hard look at
the water

51:13.670 --> 51:15.739 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
crisis in Flint, Michigan.

51:15.772 --> 51:20.544 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
"Poisoned Water" uses the lens
of science
to reveal how the water disaster
in Flint

51:20.577 --> 51:25.482 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
brought to light the many
vulnerabilities
of water systems across the
country, including

51:25.515 --> 51:29.519 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
the amount of lead in pipes
leading to individual
homes.

51:29.553 --> 51:37.160 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
NARRATOR: If there is so much
lead in our
plumbing, why aren't we all
lead-poisoned?

51:37.194 --> 51:44.067 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The answer lies in the complex
chemical reactions
that go on between the pipe
itself and the

51:44.101 --> 51:46.103 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
water flowing through it.

51:46.136 --> 51:49.940 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MAN: Inside the pipe, as the
water goes through,
it reacts.

51:49.973 --> 51:53.343 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Chemical reactions take place
with the plumbing
material.

51:53.376 --> 51:59.349 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And this begins to build up kind
of a protective
coating, what we call a scale.

51:59.382 --> 52:02.919 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
NARRATOR: This protective scale
is crucial.

52:02.953 --> 52:14.231 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
It becomes a barrier that
prevents lead from
leaching into the water.

52:14.264 --> 52:19.769 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
As scientists at the EPA's
Office of Research
and Development reveal, this
protective scale

52:19.803 --> 52:24.174 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
can be made of up to 90 percent
lead.

52:24.207 --> 52:30.413 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MAN: Most people don't expect
that there's
actually a lot of lead in the
scale.

52:30.447 --> 52:36.052 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
It's not a very good joke, but
we often say
that you are drinking water
through lead-painted

52:36.086 --> 52:40.157 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
straws, because these are the
minerals that
were in lead paint, and yet
they're lining

52:40.190 --> 52:41.892 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
your drinking water pipe.

52:41.925 --> 52:46.630 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
You're using lead to protect
yourself from
lead.

52:46.663 --> 52:54.738 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
NARRATOR: To control pipe
corrosion, water
utilities often add a chemical
that helps

52:54.771 --> 53:03.046 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
build up the scale and protect
the water.

53:03.079 --> 53:09.419 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
This is so critical that EPA's
lead and copper
rule requires cities with over
50,000 people

53:09.452 --> 53:16.760 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
to have what's called
corrosion-control treatment
in place.

53:16.793 --> 53:24.501 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The question is, has the city of
Flint been
using corrosion control?

